she was dazzled by hades and was about to seduce him had not queen persephone intervened and metamorphosed minthe , in the words of strabo 's account , " into the garden mint , which some call hedyosmon ( lit . ' sweet - smelling')".strabo , geographica viii.3.14 .

ancient greek salad : this god came up from the underworld to woo minthe , who wound up in edible form as mint

